        <updateDate>2005-05-27T19:23:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Ferry Safety Enhancement Act of 2005 - Amends Federal shipping law to treat as a passenger vessel any vessel that carries more than 399 passengers.</p> <p>Directs the Secretary of the department in which the Coast Guard is operating to: (1) prescribe regulations that require such passenger vessels be equipped with a voyage data recorder; and (2) require vessel pilots to submit their annual physical examination results to the Coast Guard. Sets forth a criminal penalty for persons who falsify physical examination reports.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Ferry Safety Enhancement Act of 2005</title>
